			<div id="post-2341" class="post-2341 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-holiday-recipes tag-game-day-recipes tag-recipes">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/holiday-recipes/cirro-energy-win-big-with-these-easy-game-day-recipes/" title="Permalink to Cirro Energy | Win Big with these Easy Game-Day Recipes" rel="bookmark">Cirro Energy | Win Big with these Easy Game-Day Recipes</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/holiday-recipes/cirro-energy-win-big-with-these-easy-game-day-recipes/" title="10:50 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">February 2, 2016</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/author/stephen/" title="View all posts by Cirro Energy">Cirro Energy</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>The game of the year is almost here. Whether you’re hosting a watch party or joining the guest list, these three recipes are guaranteed to make you the MVP of the night.</p>
<p><strong>Guac-a-dog</strong></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2343" src="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/guaca-252x300.jpg" alt="guaca" width="252" height="300" srcset="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/guaca-252x300.jpg 252w, http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/guaca.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 252px) 100vw, 252px" /></p>
<p><strong>These hot dogs with a twist are sure to be a game-day favorite.  </strong></p>
<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>4 </strong>hot dogs</li>
<li><strong>1 </strong>avocado, peeled and pitted</li>
<li><strong>1 </strong>tablespoon fresh lime juice</li>
<li>kosher salt and black pepper</li>
<li><strong>4 </strong>hot dog buns, split</li>
<li><strong>4 </strong>small romaine lettuce leaves</li>
<li><strong>¼ </strong>small red onion, chopped</li>
<li>hot sauce for drizzling</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Prepare the hot dogs following package instructions.</li>
<li>In a bowl, mash the avocado and combine it with the lime juice. Sprinkle with ¼ teaspoon each of salt and black pepper.</li>
<li>Set the hot dog buns on a serving dish, and place a hot dog in each.</li>
<li>Top each hot dog with the lettuce, avocado mixture and onion. For an extra kick, sprinkle with hot sauce.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Image and recipe from </strong><a href="http://www.realsimple.com/food-recipes/browse-all-recipes/guacamole-hot-dog"><strong>realsimple.com</strong></a></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Kickin’ chicken wings</strong></p>
<p><strong><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2342" src="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/chik-252x300.jpg" alt="chik" width="252" height="300" srcset="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/chik-252x300.jpg 252w, http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/chik.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 252px) 100vw, 252px" /></strong></p>
<p><strong>F</strong><strong>ull of flavor and grilled, these wings are ready to make their watch-party debut. </strong></p>
<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>8 </strong>chicken wings (about 1 ½ pounds), halved through the joint</li>
<li><strong>1 </strong>teaspoon olive oil</li>
<li><strong>2 </strong>teaspoons seafood seasoning</li>
<li><strong>3 </strong>tablespoons unsalted butter, melted</li>
<li>ranch dressing, for dipping</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Heat grill until it reaches a medium heat setting. In a bowl, combine and toss the wings, olive oil and 1 teaspoon of seasoning. Grill the wings uncovered, and turn over to cook the other side. Grill for 15 to 20 minutes until cooked through.</li>
<li>In another bowl, mix the last teaspoon of seafood seasoning with the butter. Add the wings to the mixture and toss. Serve with ranch dressing.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Image and recipe from </strong><a href="http://www.realsimple.com/food-recipes/browse-all-recipes/grilled-spiced-chicken-wings"><strong>realsimple.com</strong></a></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Guiltless Baked Sweet Potato</strong></p>
<p><strong> <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2344" src="http://blog.cirroenergy.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/potato-252x300.jpg" alt="potato" width="252" height="300" /></strong></p>
<p><strong>This flavorful option is sure to satisfy the vegetarians of the bunch. </strong></p>
<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>4 </strong>large sweet potatoes</li>
<li><strong>2 </strong>tablespoons canola oil</li>
<li>kosher salt and black pepper</li>
<li><strong>2 </strong>tablespoons olive oil</li>
<li><strong>1 </strong>avocado, sliced</li>
<li><strong>¼ </strong>cup chopped pecans, toasted</li>
<li><strong>¼ </strong>cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley leaves</li>
<li><strong>4 </strong>ounces fresh goat cheese, crumbled (about 1 cup)</li>
<li>green salad, for serving</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Heat oven until it reaches 400° F. Brush sweet potatoes using canola oil, and add ¼ teaspoon of salt. Using a rimmed baking sheet, bake for 40 to 50 minutes until tender.</li>
<li>Split each potato open, and sprinkle with olive oil. Add ½ teaspoon of salt and pepper.</li>
<li>Complete the loaded sweet potatoes by adding avocado, pecans, parsley and goat cheese on top.</li>
<li>Dress the dish with a salad.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Image and recipe from </strong><a href="http://www.realsimple.com/food-recipes/browse-all-recipes/loaded-baked-sweet-potato"><strong>realsimple.com</strong></a></p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
